    <h3>Why SmartSweets Sour Worms Are Our Top Pick</h3>

    <p>SmartSweets Sour Blast Buddies deliver the most satisfying sour gummy worm experience at the lowest sugar cost. With only 3 grams of sugar per bag — compared to 19 grams per serving in Trolli Sour Brite Crawlers — they represent an 84% sugar reduction. The sour coating uses the same citric acid and malic acid blend as conventional sour candy, so the initial mouth-puckering tang is equally intense. Each worm features a two-tone, dual-flavor design that replicates the classic sour worm experience.</p>

    <p>The texture is softer than gelatin worms — this is the only meaningful compromise. Pectin does not achieve the same rubbery chew resistance as gelatin, and in an elongated worm shape, that difference is more noticeable than in compact gummy bears. However, the sour coating dominates the sensory experience to the point where texture takes a back seat. In our testing, SmartSweets Sour Worms scored highest in "sour satisfaction" — the combination of initial sourness intensity and sweet flavor payoff that defines great sour candy. For more SmartSweets products, see our broader <a href="/candy/">vegan gummy candy</a> hub page.</p>

