    <!-- FAQ -->
    <section class="faq-sec">
      <h2>Vegan Gummy Worms — Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <details class="fq"><summary>Are regular gummy worms vegan?</summary><p>No. Most mainstream gummy worms (Trolli, Haribo, store brands) contain gelatin from animal collagen, plus beeswax and carmine. Vegan worms use pectin, agar-agar, or starch instead.</p></details>
      <details class="fq"><summary>What is the best sour vegan gummy worm?</summary><p>SmartSweets Sour Blast Buddies for low sugar (3g) with intense sourness. For organic, Surf Sweets delivers the cleanest ingredients. For maximum sourness, Project 7.</p></details>
      <details class="fq"><summary>Do vegan gummy worms have the same sour coating as regular gummy worms?</summary><p>Yes. The sour coating (citric acid, malic acid) is plant-derived in all gummy worms. Vegan and conventional sour worms use the same acids, so sourness is comparable.</p></details>
      <details class="fq"><summary>Are Trolli Sour Brite Crawlers vegan?</summary><p>No. Trolli contains gelatin, artificial colors (Red 40, Yellow 5, Blue 1), and artificial flavors. The best vegan alternative is SmartSweets Sour Blast Buddies.</p></details>
      <details class="fq"><summary>Why do vegan gummy worms taste different from regular gummy worms?</summary><p>The main difference is texture (softer pectin vs chewier gelatin), not flavor. The sour coating is identical. Some vegan brands taste more natural because they use real fruit juice instead of synthetic flavoring.</p></details>
      <details class="fq"><summary>Are vegan gummy worms healthier than regular gummy worms?</summary><p>SmartSweets (3g sugar) and Project 7 (4g sugar) are significantly healthier than Trolli (19g sugar/serving). Organic options eliminate synthetic dyes. But not all vegan worms are lower in sugar.</p></details>
      <details class="fq"><summary>Can I get organic vegan gummy worms?</summary><p>Yes. Surf Sweets, YumEarth, Wholesome, and Black Forest all make USDA Organic vegan gummy worms with pectin-based formulations.</p></details>
      <details class="fq"><summary>Where can I buy vegan gummy worms?</summary><p>Amazon (widest selection and best multi-pack pricing), Whole Foods, Target, Walmart, and Sprouts. SmartSweets and YumEarth have the widest retail distribution.</p></details>
